# Selecting Elements üîç

How to "grab" an element from HTML.

```javascript
// By ID (Fastest)
const title = document.getElementById('main-title');

// By Class
const items = document.getElementsByClassName('item');

// Key Selectors (Most modern)
const box = document.querySelector('.box'); // Selects FIRST match
const allBoxes = document.querySelectorAll('.box'); // Selects ALL matches
```

# Changing Content ‚úèÔ∏è

```javascript
const heading = document.querySelector('h1');

// Change Text
heading.innerText = "New Title";

// Change HTML (Be careful with security!)
heading.innerHTML = "<span>Styled</span> Title";

// Change Attributes
const img = document.querySelector('img');
img.src = "new-pic.jpg";

// Change Styles
heading.style.color = "blue";
heading.style.fontSize = "50px";
```
